ry fully into the mystery genre. The action of the narrative plays out in a very creative and cinematic way, creating instant images in the readers imagination as they follow the adventure piece by piece. The way the author stretches out the mystery is perfect as well, taking readers in one direction and then completely dropping the floor out from under them, taking the adventure into an entirely unexpected direction. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThe Verdict\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThis is a wonderful novel, filled to the brim with action, suspense and romance as one lone detective becomes embroiled in a larger than life international mystery. Who can you trust when everyone seems to be connected? And with a feeling of dread hanging over the detective after the loss of his last two relationships, can he find happiness in a new relationship, or are the dangers of the case too overwhelming for his relationship to survive? Find out in this incredible roller coaster mystery by picking up your copy of The Scopas Factor by Vincent Panettiere today!","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/23843936?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2733757476"},"likeCount":0,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:15832966":{"id":15832966,"__typename":"User","legacyId":15832966,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1372096638i/15832966.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":13,"viewableName":"Kim","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/15832966-kim","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":0},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.14dt0-Vb_HgWJyBtfCh2wg":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.14dt0-Vb_HgWJyBtfCh2wg","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.S33TI2hgoGzk3mSlakcc1A"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:15832966"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1548866728371,"createdAt":1548866681584,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1548866727832,"text":"The Scopas Factor, by Vincent Panettiere, is an ambitious story full of adventure and intrigue. The book starts in 1990 in the Ban Vinai Refugee Camp in Thailand. The refugees are from the Hmong exodus from Northern Laos, fleeing from the Communist insurgents. One woman, known as the mud woman, refuses to live inside with the others and spends her days tracing pictures in the dirt. One day, Mos, her daughter, shows up and is reunited with her mother. While they are in the camp, the mud woman sews a recreation of the massacre in their village. After the mud woman finishes the cloth and shows Mos where she hid it, a truck of heavily armed men invade the camp and take her. Also, in 1990, we meet Tom Fitzgerald. He is a young college graduate who answers an ad to be sent to Thailand. From there, he is sent to Ban Vinai. He arrives two days after the old woman is taken. He meets and falls in love with Mos. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eWe then skip to twenty-five years later in Arles, France, where David St. Pierre finds himself in trouble. He is an art forger who cannot deliver what he has promised to a dangerous man known as The Black. The item in question is the Hmong story cloth that the mud woman made. If he cannot get the cloth to them, he will be killed. After storming out of a lunch with his wife, Alexis, and his friend, Thornie, David disappears. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eJump to Chicago, where we meet Detective Mike Hegan who has a history of getting the women he loves killed. He is dating Diana, who accompanies him on a trip to California where he will go to an interview for the police chief job and then on to meet her parents. Once in California, the story comes full circle as we find that the mayor of the little town is Tom Fitzgerald. He is married to Mos and has children with her. From there, we find that everyone is connected and involved. The Hmong cloth disappears and the chase is on to find it and to bring the bad guys to justice. The question of who the bad guys really are is featured heavily in the story. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThe book is very easy to read. The writing is well done and the story flows. I found myself very interested in what would happen next. One issue I had with the story is that there was almost too much going on. There were so many characters that it was a bit difficult to keep up. The only other thing I did not like is that some of the language was a bit antiquated. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI am giving the book a solid 4 out of 5 because I really enjoyed the story. I would recommend it to anyone who likes adventurous mystery stories with a lot going on. This engaging novel definitely fits the bill. \u003cbr /\u003e","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/15832966?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2675127788"},"likeCount":0,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.1BNr5t3FmjZTjG1aN5TTPg":{"id":"kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.1BNr5t3FmjZTjG1aN5TTPg","__typename":"Contributor","works":{"__typename":"ContributorWorksConnection","totalCount":1}},"User:20102989":{"id":20102989,"__typename":"User","legacyId":20102989,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1542851316i/20102989._UX200_CR0,33,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":true,"textReviewsCount":95,"viewableName":"Sarah Nantais","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/20102989-sarah-nantais","contributor":{"__ref":"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.1BNr5t